jchrest.domainSpecifics.fixations

Class HypothesisDiscriminationFixation

  • java.lang.Object
    • jchrest.domainSpecifics.Fixation
      • jchrest.domainSpecifics.fixations.HypothesisDiscriminationFixation

  • public class HypothesisDiscriminationFixation
extends Fixation
    Represents a Fixation made using the "hypothesis-discrimination" heuristic (see "Perception and Memory in Chess" by de Groot and Gobet, section 8.7.6). NOTE: HypothesisDiscriminationFixations do not require any Fixations to have been added by the Perceiver associated with the Chrest model that invokes #this#make( jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, int) prior to this invocation in order to propose a Square to fixate on. However, the Chrest model that invokes #this#make( jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, int) must have at least 1 Node in its Modality.VISUAL Stm at the time specified when #this#make(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, int) is invoked.

    • Method Detail

      • make

        public Square make(Scene scene,
                   int time)
        Implements the procedure of making #this according to the fixation 1 description provided in section 8.7.6 of "Perception and Memory in Chess" by de Groot and Gobet.
        Specified by:
        make in class Fixation
        Parameters:
        scene -
        time -
        Returns:
        The Square represented by invoking ItemSquarePattern.getColumn() and ItemSquarePattern.getRow() on the first ItemSquarePattern of the image of the first child of the current Modality.VISUAL Stm hypothesis of the Chrest model invoking this method at the time specified. However, if any of the following statements evaluate to Boolean.TRUE, null is returned:
        1. The scene specified is entirely blind.
        2. The result of invoking Stm.getCount(int) on the Modality.VISUAL Stm of the Chrest model making #this at the time specified is equal to null or 0.
        3. The result of invoking Node.getChildren( int) on the Modality.VISUAL Stm hypothesis of the Chrest model making #this at the time specified is equal to null or is empty.
        4. The result of invoking Link.getTest() on the Link of the first child of the Modality.VISUAL Stm hypothesis of the Chrest model making #this at the time specified is equal to null or is not an instance of ItemSquarePattern.
        5. The Square specified by the first ItemSquarePattern in the result of invoking Link.getTest() on the Link of the first child of the Modality.VISUAL Stm hypothesis of the Chrest model making #this at the time specified is:
          • Equal to null or is not an instance of ItemSquarePattern.
          • The same Square that was fixated on in the Fixation previous to this.
          • Is not a valid coordinate in context of the result of invoking jchrest.architecture.Perceiver#getCurrentScene() on the Perceiver associated with the Chrest model that is making #this.
          • Is blind in context of the result of invoking jchrest.architecture.Perceiver#getCurrentScene() on the Perceiver associated with the Chrest model that is making #this.
        6. The time specified is earlier than the result of invoking #this#getPerformanceTime().
